Description: Fragment of strap handle of East Greek (perhaps South Ionian) pottery oenochoe; orange clay with much silver mica; cream slip, red-brown fired glaze; bands at top and bottom inside and out; further daubs on inside; sign scratched on the outside.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIII, no. 368)
Johnston 2006a / Trademarks on Greek Vases: Addenda (East Greek 197) (Entry should be 198)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GE.062)
